overnments who want to monitor individuals on probation and keep tract of certain types of offenders. The second customer group is businesses that want to monitor the whereabouts of their decision makers. Business owners are also tired of not knowing where their salesmen are on a Friday afternoon. The third customer group is parents - primarily mothers, who want to know where their children are - all the time. These three customer groups will propel the synergy of location seasors, smart, agile wireless hardware and software and low-cost networks. These sensor driven networks can vary from large, sophisticated, computer controlled systems to small data gathering networks, operating in the developing world. Especially in the developing world, these sensors will largely operate in wireless local area networks (WLANs) connected to simple, satellite ground terminals. These sensor networks will have little or no latency requirements and thus will be especially satellite friendly. This new revolution of chip-driven, wireless, low cost sensors, networks and applications will provide important new markets for communications satellites.},
